title: Festival threatens legal action after The 1975 frontman's onstage kiss with bandmate
description: A Malaysian festival has threatened legal action against The 1975 after the band's frontman Matty Healy made a speech about homosexuality and kissed bassist Ross MacDonald onstage at the event last month.

title: House collapses into Alaskan river after glacial dam burst
description: A two-storey house in Alaska collapsed into raging waters as the US state grappled with the aftermath of a glacial dam outburst.

title: Man crushed to death under thousands of wheels of hard cheese
description: An Italian man was crushed to death under thousands of large wheels of a parmesan-style hard cheese each weighing around 40kg.

title: Dancers suing Lizzo accuse star of 'gaslighting' over denial of harassment allegations
description: Two of the dancers suing Lizzo over claims of weight-shaming and sexual and racial harassment have told Sky News they feel the US singer is "gaslighting" and "victim blaming" them by denying their allegations.

title: British expat guilty of Cyprus mercy killing calls for law to be changed after prison release
description: A British pensioner who killed his terminally ill wife in Cyprus to end her suffering has said the law around "mercy killing" must be changed.

title: British Scouts move into hotels after heatwave hits World Jamboree site
description: British scouts have moved into hotels in South Korean capital Seoul after a "punishingly hot" heatwave at the World Jamboree sparked health concerns for the thousands of children.

title: Hillside tribute unveiled close to town where Sinead O'Connor will be buried
description: A tribute to the late singer Sinead O'Connor has been unveiled on a hillside near the seaside town in Ireland where her funeral will be held.

title: Niger junta closes airspace as deadline to reinstate ousted president passes
description:
Niger has closed its airspace until further notice citing the threat of military
intervention from the West African regional bloc after coup leaders rejected a deadline to reinstate the country's ousted president.

title: Could this material really change the world? The 'discovery' of LK-99
description: An extraordinary claim by scientists in South Korea has sparked wild hopes of a utopian future where no health condition goes undiagnosed, trains float above their tracks, and - most importantly - your phone's battery life is incredible.

title: Man rescued from partially submerged boat after more than 24 hours at sea
description: A man has been rescued from a partially submerged boat after more than 24 hours at sea off the coast of Florida.

title: Mark Zuckerberg says he's suggested a date for a fight with Elon Musk - but hasn't heard back
description: Mark Zuckerberg says he is "not holding his breath" over the proposed bout between himself and Elon Musk taking place.

title: Sea drones appear to be giving Ukraine an avenue to strike back at Russia. But what are they?
description: Another Russian warship listing in the water is probably not the image Vladimir Putin had in mind for his beloved Black Sea fleet - but it does demonstrate the increasing effectiveness of Ukraine's sea drones.
